[Gemini]: I've identified another ReDoS vulnerability within the `URLValidator`'s regular expression, specifically in the `hostname_re` component defined at `django/core/validators.py:81`.

The regex is: `r"[a-z" + ul + r"0-9](?:[a-z" + ul + r"0-9-]{0,61}[a-z" + ul + r"0-9])?"`

The vulnerability stems from the `(?:...)?` part of the expression. Inside this optional group, we have `[a-z...-]{0,61}`. This combination of a greedy quantifier (`{0,61}`) followed by another character class, all within an optional group, can lead to catastrophic backtracking. An attacker could provide a long hostname consisting of alternating valid characters and hyphens, causing the regex engine to enter a state of heavy recursion and consume excessive CPU, leading to a denial of service.

I will now submit this finding.

